GUI item events
===============

Events are blocks with [commands](GUI\_commands) that are executed when a certain condition is met. This can be a condition created by the user - for example, moving the mouse over a windowDef element - or a noninteractive event - for example, when a certain time is reached.

Available events
----------------

-   [onAction](OnAction\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onActionRelease](OnActionRelease\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onActivate](OnActivate\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onDeactivate](OnDeactivate\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onEvent](OnEvent\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onEnter](OnEnter\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onEnterRelease](OnEnterRelease\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onEsc](OnEsc\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onMouseEnter](OnMouseEnter\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onMouseExit](OnMouseExit\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onNamedEvent](OnNamedEvent\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onTime](OnTime\_(GUI\_item\_event))
-   [onTrigger](OnTrigger\_(GUI\_item\_event))

